I am trying to go again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look good right now, but it's only Monday.
It is already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be EXTREMELY difficult to get medical approval due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It is not impossible, but it will take EXTREMELY long and mean a LOT of extra work.
Although this is somewhat discouraging, it is still just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what is ahead for me.
The FAA is no fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you a medical approval if you take medication against it.
